#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:17
msgid ""
"One of the features of the Markdown language that make it widely used in "
"writing technical documentation is its convertibility. Code can be converted "
"for display in many formats (HTML, PDF, plain text,..), therefore making "
"content usable in numerous scenarios."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:19
msgid ""
"Specifically, documentation written for Rocky Linux is converted to `HTML` "
"using a *python* application. The application converts documents written in "
"*markdown* to static HTML pages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:21
msgid ""
"The problem arises when writing your documentation for Rocky Linux, of "
"verifying its correct display when converted to `HTML` code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:23
msgid ""
"To integrate this functionality into your editor, two of the plugins "
"available for this purpose, [toppair/peek.nvim](https://github.com/toppair/"
"peek.nvim) and [markdown-preview.nvim](https://github.com/iamcco/markdown-"
"preview.nvim), will be illustrated on this page. Both of these support "
"*github-style*, the choice of browser to use for preview, and synchronized "
"scrolling with the editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Peek.nvim"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:27
msgid ""
"[Peek](https://github.com/toppair/peek.nvim) uses [Deno](https://deno.com/"
"manual) a JavaScript, TypeScript and WebAssembly runtime with default secure "
"settings for its operation. By default Deno does not allow any file, network "
"or environment access unless explicitly enabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:29
msgid ""
"If you have also installed the [Template Chadrc](../template_chadrc.md) this "
"component will already be available as it is one of the language servers "
"installed by default. In case it is not yet present in the editor you can "
"install it with the command `:MasonInstall deno`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:31
msgid "!!! Warning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The language server **must** be installed before proceeding to install the plugin. Otherwise the installation will fail and it will be necessary to remove the code from **/custom/plugins.lua**, perform a configuration cleanup by opening `Lazy` and typing <kbd>X</kbd> to delete the plugin and then repeat the installation procedure.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:35
msgid ""
"To install the plugin you will have to edit the file **/custom/plugins.lua** "
"by adding the following block of code:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"toppair/peek.nvim\",\n"
"    build = \"deno task --quiet build:fast\",\n"
"    keys = {\n"
"        {\n"
"        \"<leader>op\",\n"
"            function()\n"
"            local peek = require(\"peek\")\n"
"                if peek.is_open() then\n"
"            peek.close()\n"
"            else\n"
"            peek.open()\n"
"            end\n"
"        end,\n"
"        desc = \"Peek (Markdown Preview)\",\n"
"        },\n"
"},\n"
"    opts = { theme = \"dark\", app = \"browser\" },\n"
"},\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have saved the file you can perform its installation by opening the plugins manager interface with the `:Lazy` command. The plugins manager will have already recognized it automatically and will allow you to install it by typing <kbd>I</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:61
msgid ""
"To get the full functionality, however, you must close NvChad (*nvim*) and "
"reopen it. This is to allow the editor to load those of **Peek** into the "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Its configuration already includes the command to activate it `<leader>op` which on the keyboard translates to <kbd>Space</kbd> + <kbd>o</kbd> followed by <kbd>p</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:65
msgid "![Peek](./images/peek_command.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:67
msgid "You also have the string:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "opts = { theme = \"dark\", app = \"browser\" },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:73
msgid ""
"Which allows you to pass options for the light or dark theme of the preview "
"and the method to be used for display."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:75
msgid ""
"In this configuration, the \"browser\" method was chosen, which opens the "
"file to be viewed in the system's default browser, but the plugin allows "
"through the \"webview\" method to preview the file using only **Deno** via "
"the [webview_deno](https://github.com/webview/webview_deno) component."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:77
msgid "![Peek Webview](./images/peek_webview.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Markdown-preview.nvim"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:81
msgid ""
"[Markdown-preview.nvim](https://github.com/iamcco/markdown-preview.nvim) is "
"a plugin written in `node.js` (JavaScript). Its installation on NvChad does "
"not require any dependencies as the developers provide a precompiled version "
"that works perfectly in the editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:83
msgid ""
"To install this version you will need to add this code block to your **/"
"custom/plugins.lua**:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"iamcco/markdown-preview.nvim\",\n"
"    cmd = {\"MarkdownPreview\", \"MarkdownPreviewStop\"},\n"
"    lazy = false,\n"
"    build = function() vim.fn[\"mkdp#util#install\"]() end,\n"
"    init = function()\n"
"        vim.g.mkdp_theme = 'dark'\n"
"    end\n"
"},\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:97
msgid ""
"As with the previous plugin, you will need to close the editor and reopen it "
"to give NvChad a chance to load the new configuration. Again you can pass to "
"the plugin some custom options described in the [dedicated section](https://"
"github.com/iamcco/markdown-preview.nvim#markdownpreview-config) of the "
"project repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:99
msgid ""
"However, the options must be modified to fit the configuration of `lazy."
"nvim`, particularly the option configured in this example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "vim.g.mkdp_theme = 'dark'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:105
msgid "It corresponds to the option described on the project site as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "let g:mkdp_theme = 'dark'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:111
msgid ""
"As you can see, to set the options you will have to modify the initial part "
"of them to make them interpretable. To give another example let us take the "
"option that allows you to choose which browser to use for the preview that "
"is specified like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "let g:mkdp_browser = '/usr/bin/chromium-browser'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:117
msgid ""
"To interpret this correctly in NvChad it will have to be modified by "
"replacing `let g:` with `vim.g.`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "vim.g.mkdp_browser = '/usr/bin/chromium-browser'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:124
msgid ""
"This way the next time NvChad is opened, `chromium-browser` will be used "
"regardless of the system's default browser."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:126
msgid ""
"The configuration also provides the commands `:MarkdownPreview` and `:"
"MarkdownPreviewStop` to open and close the preview, respectively. For faster "
"access to the commands you can map them to the **/custom/mapping.lua** file "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"-- binding for Markdown Preview\n"
"M.mdpreview = {\n"
"  n = {\n"
"    [\"<leader>mp\"] = { \"<cmd> MarkdownPreview<CR>\", \"Open Preview\"},\n"
"    [\"<leader>mc\"] = { \"<cmd> MarkdownPreviewStop<CR>\", \"Close Preview\"},\n"
"    },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "This will allow you to open the markdown preview by typing <kbd>Enter</kbd> + <kbd>m</kbd> followed by <kbd>p</kbd> and close it with the combination <kbd>Enter</kbd> + <kbd>m</kbd> followed by <kbd>c</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:140
msgid "!!! Note"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The plugin also provides the command `:MarkdownPreviewToggle` but at the time of writing this document it does not seem to work properly. If you try to invoke it, it will not change the preview theme but will open a new browser Tab with the same preview.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:144
msgid "![Markdown Preview](./images/markdown_preview_nvim.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conclusions and final thoughts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:148
msgid ""
"A preview of what you are writing can be useful, both for those new to this "
"editor and for those with a more in-depth knowledge of the Markdown "
"language. The preview allows you to assess the impact of the code once "
"converted, and any errors it contains."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:150
msgid ""
"The choice of which plugin to use is totally subjective, and we encourage "
"you to try both to assess which one might be best for you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/md_preview.md:151
msgid ""
"The use of one of these plugins allows you to contribute documents to the "
"documentation on Rocky Linux that conform to the code used therefore "
"alleviating the work of documentation reviewers."
msgstr ""
